\begin_layout Standard
Ferdinando proposed to solve Bitcoin's inelasticity issue by simply inverting
 the supply-demand curves' logic to our advantage.
 With the usage of smart contracts, it is easy to program a monetary policy
 that keeps the purchasing power of the underlying token stable by 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

rebasing
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 the token.
 Rebasing means that we expand and contract the supply of the token to maintain
 price parity.
 As is shown in the schematic below:
